**Prutha** — *spotting the banners, calling out*
> "Eastern Heart! Three banners on the wall! I see one! Sun and Stone! My uncle's clan march! They are family!"

---

**[Prutha's Dawn-Bow at the Gate]**
- Prutha walks to the palisade alone at a deliberate pace, hands open, and performs the dawn-bow at thirty feet from the gate.
- He pulls a bone whistle from his armor and blows the dawn prayer.
- The sentry lowers her bow and returns the gesture, shouts to the rest of the band, and relays Prutha's answer back to the party.

**GM** — *narrating Prutha's approach*
> "He approaches the Palisade alone at a deliberate pace, hands open. At 30 feet from the gate, he performs the dawn-bow. Right fist to left shoulder, head down. He pulls…"
> "The bone whistled from inside his armor and blows the dawn prayer."
> "the Palisade, whoever's there lowers her bow and retunes the bow. She shouts to him in orcish, he answers. Then she yells to the rest of the band, and yells back to him."
> "bring your drow, bring your Aasimar, bring all of them. We are listening."

**Vukradin** — *reacting*
> "Sure, why not?"

**Wade Brown** — *flatly*
> "It's a trap."

**Vukradin** — *undeterred*
> "It's a trap, but I'll go anyway."

